High-level comparison (what the numbers say)
- ResNet50 is better by every main aggregate metric: IoU (+~0.083), Accuracy (+~0.025), F1 (+~0.064). That’s a meaningful margin.
    - If you rank purely by segmentation quality on this dataset, ResNet50 wins.
- MobileNetV2 sacrifices quality for compactness/speed: IoU and F1 are noticeably lower. This is exactly the typical tradeoff — MobileNetV2 is lighter and faster but less expressive than ResNet50 for dense segmentation.
- All F1 / Precision / Recall numbers are quite low (~0.34–0.41) compared to IoU/Accuracy which are very high (IoU 0.95 / 0.87). This is unusual and important — it points to either a class-imbalance / metric-definition effect or a bug in metric computation.